description: Republican Kelly Ayotte's victory in New Hampshire will bring the total number of women holding governor’s offices to 13 — surpassing the previous high of 12 set in 2023.
title: 13 states will have women governors next year, a new record

description: The versatile actor had hundreds of screen credits to his name, including Platoon, The Rock and Final Destination.
title: 'Candyman' star Tony Todd dies at 69

description: Qatar has decided to suspend its key mediation efforts between Hamas and Israel, officials said Saturday. The announcement comes after growing frustration with the lack of progress on a deal.
title: Officials say Qatar has decided to suspend its mediation efforts on Gaza

description: There's an area in China that's home to a huge trove of dinosaur fossils. It used to be thought it was formed through a Pompeii-like volcanic eruption, stopping dinosaurs in their tracks. But new evidence has come to light about how it likely came to be.
title: Dinosaurs unearthed in China may have ended with a collapse, not a catastrophe

description: NPR's Scott Simon accompanied his daughters to the polls, as they voted in their first presidential election.
title: Opinion: Witnessing my daughters' first votes was a moment to remember

description: We look at the various threats sent to polling places on election day this week, as well as the extent to which foreign actors tried to interfere with the presidential election.
title: Foreign Interference Recap

description: Data from a large survey of U.S. voters found that a significant subset of voters who supported abortion rights ballot measures also voted for Trump.
title: They split the ticket. Meet the abortion rights voters who also went for Trump

description: Chinese business people may be able to find creative ways to avoid U.S. tariffs, but for Beijing, its concerns for the incoming Trump presidency go beyond trade.
title: From Taiwan to technology, China ponders what's to come under Trump 2.0

description: The findings, which used DNA from the plaster casts of people who died in the Mt. Vesuvius eruption two millennia ago, challenge the traditional gender and familial assumptions about the Pompeiians.
title: New DNA evidence upends what we thought we knew about Pompeii victims

description: The presidential election is over, and the complicated two-month sprint has begun to hand over the levers of power from one administration to the next.
title: The transition to the Trump administration is underway. But it’s already behind

description: Election deniers have spent the past four years focused on false claims that 2020 was rigged. This year, it raised similar alarms about fraud — only for those claims to evaporate as returns came in.
title: 2020’s debunked election fraud claims are coming back due to Trump’s 2024 victory

description: Within two days after Election Day, right-wing activists and two Republican state lawmakers in Pennsylvania withdrew thousands of last-minute challenges to voters’ absentee ballot applications.
title: Mail ballot challenges are dropped in Pennsylvania shortly after Election Day

description: Piano lessons and soccer practice can encourage grit. But if your kid isn’t into it, it can become a stress-inducing obligation. Here’s how to have hard conversations with your child about quitting.
title: Why it’s so hard for parents to let their kid quit
